        }
      ],
      "markdown": "$$\\begin{array}{cccc}x_{1}&-2x_{2}&+x_{3}&=0\\\\&2x_{2}&-8x_{3}&=8\\\\&-3x_{2}&+13x_{3}&=-9\\\\\\end{array}\\quad 解 \\quad\\begin{bmatrix}1&-2&1&0\\\\0&2&-8&8\\\\0&-3&13&-9\\\\\\end{bmatrix}$$\n\nChanging the coefficient of $x_{2}$ from 2 to 1.\n\nThe purpose of this step ois tosimliy the calculation in the next steps.\n\n\n\nTo do it, we multiply the $2^{n d}$ equation by ½/2.\n\n$$\\begin{array}{ccc}x_{1}&-2x_{2}&+x_{3}\\\\&x_{2}&-4x_{3}\\\\&-3x_{2}&+13x_{3}\\\\\\end{array}\\begin{array}{ccc}=0\\\\=4\\\\=-9\\\\\\end{array}\\quad\\begin{array}{ccc}\\begin{bmatrix}1&-2&1&0\\\\0&1&-4&4\\\\0&-3&13&-9\\\\\\end{bmatrix}.$$",
